parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blind spot monitoring system can cause the driver to be unaware of vehicles in their blind spot, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The passenger side blind spot monitoring light stays on even when no cars are next to the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the emissions system can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
the vehicle loses power and turns off
and the vehicle's brakes
anti-lock brakes
power steering
stability track
and battery saver indicators illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heated steering wheel can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the driver, especially in cold weather.
symptoms: The heated steering wheel stops working
and the fuse blows repeatedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning compressor can cause the vehicle's air conditioning system to malfunction, making the vehicle uncomfortable to drive.
symptoms: The air conditioning compressor stops getting power
and hot air blows out of the vents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the audio system can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The sound system stops working
and there is no sound from the radio
blinker
or door open warnings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn assembly can cause the driver to be unable to alert other drivers or pedestrians, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The horn does not sound when pressing the horn icons on the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbags to Deploy in Crash Situations
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in crash situations can increase the risk of injury or fatality to occupants, as they are designed to provide critical protection in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Airbag warning lights illuminate on the dashboard
airbag failure to deploy in a crash
seatbelts engage but airbags do not deploy
crash damage to the vehicle without airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power steering can make it difficult to control the vehicle, especially at high speeds, which can increase the risk of accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The driver information center displays a "Power Steering Failure" warning
the power steering system becomes unavailable
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the vehicle requires greater effort to make turns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine power can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of control, especially when driving at high speeds, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle loses all power without warning
the engine turns off completely
no power steering or electrical indications of a problem are shown on the dashboard
the vehicle restarts without any problems after being placed in park.
